sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K986001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a main part in the genetic circuit. With a ppk, RBS and a promoter it can be a whole genetic circuit. Can be used for dissolving phosphorus in water.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kang Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We think that it can be very useful in the whole genetic circuit. During the research everything goes fine.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: PPK
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: This is a PPK Coding Sequence which can remove phosphate from water
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a PPK CDS which is created by Jack Jia from Shenzhen_SFLS and with Eric's great help. The polyphosphatase then degrades phosphates present when there is too much phosphorus in water. We use it as a CDS in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kang Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Nothing. Everything goes on well during our research.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: mRFP (DsRed) derived, altered to be a biobrick by removing a PstI site and adding in the ends.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: ytwang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: mCherry from Roger Y. Tsien's lab, altered to be BioBrick compatible
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K737023
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter that can be induced by phosphate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Promoter that can be induced by phosphate. The downstream promoter has a single copy of the pho box, the consensus sequence shared by the pho promoters. These pho boxes are the binding sites of its corresponding response regulators phoB. Two molecules of phoB protein form a complex that could bind to the pho boxes and up-regulate the downstream expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Minghao Gong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a PPK CDS which is created by Jack Jia from Shenzhen_SFLS and with Eric's great help. The polyphosphatase then degrades phosphates present when there is too much phosphorus in water. We use it as a CDS in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kang Li
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Nothing. Everything goes on well during our research.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.
